The Black Sun Shard is a fragment of "anti-light" that fell from the sky before recorded history.
It does not create darkness. It consumes meaning: names dissolve, histories contradict, the dead remember lives they never lived.
Physical reality stays intact. The Shard attacks narrative coherence, not matter.

The Great Pyramid was built as the Shard's prison using reverse-solar geometries.
Pharaoh Ramesses accepted partial soul-binding to keep it dormant.
The Northern Pyramid serves as backup containment.
The Southern Pyramid was built to descend toward the Shard's source and learn its nature.

The Keepers of Measure's obsessive record-keeping was an anti-amnesia system built against the Shard's influence.
The entire desert civilization's insistence on encoding everything in stone was a defense against memory-erosion.

The Umbral are humanoids whose bodies partially incorporated anti-light through long habitation in Shard-adjacent spaces.
The Shard's influence still leaks through degrading seals.
It is the defining cosmic threat of the world: contained but never defeated.
